; Yamaji Family : {{ill|Yamaji Sukezumi|ja|山路主住|qq=draft|qq=draft}} became Tenmonkata in {{ill|Meiwa|ja|明和|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1 (1764). His descendants continued until the end of the Edo period. : {{ill|Yamaji Sukezumi|ja|山路主住|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – ({{ill|Yamaji Yukiyuki|ja|山路之徽|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Yamaji Tokufū|ja|山路徳風|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – {{ill|Yamaji Kanetaka|ja|山路諧孝|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – {{ill|Yamaji Akitsune|ja|山路彰常|qq=draft|qq=draft}} – ({{ill|Yamaji Akizumi|ja|山路彰善|qq=draft|qq=draft}})
