: {{ill|Sasaki Nagahide|ja|佐々木長秀|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Sasaki Nagahide|qq=}}, later {{ill|Yoshida Nagahide|ja|吉田秀長|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshida Nagahide|qq=}}, became Tenmonkata in {{ill|Meiwa|ja|明和|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiwa|qq=}} 1 (1764).
: {{ill|Yoshida Nagahide|ja|吉田秀長|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshida Nagahide|qq=}} – {{ill|Yoshida Hideaki|ja|吉田秀升|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshida Hideaki|qq=}} – {{ill|Yoshida Hideaki|ja|吉田秀賢|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshida Hideaki|qq=}} – {{ill|Yoshida Hideaki|ja|吉田秀茂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshida Hideaki|qq=}}

== Observatories ==
The first observatory, '''Sitendai''', was established in {{ill|Jōkyō|ja|貞享|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Jōkyō|qq=}} 2 (1685) in {{ill|Ushigome Wakamachi|ja|牛込藁町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ushigome Wakamachi|qq=}}. It moved to {{ill|Kanda Surugadai|ja|神田駿河台|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kanda Surugadai|qq=}} in {{ill|Genroku|ja|元禄|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Genroku|qq=}} 14 (1701) and later to {{ill|Asakusa|ja|浅草|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Asakusa|qq=}}. In {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenpō|qq=}} 13 (1842), a second observatory was established in {{ill|Kudanzaka|ja|九段坂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kudanzaka|qq=}}. Both were abolished in {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 2 (1869).

== Abolition of the Tenmonkata ==
After the {{ill|Taisei Hōkan|ja|大政奉還|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taisei Hōkan|qq=}}, responsibility for calendrical work returned to the {{ill|Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado family|qq=}}. In {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|1=Meiji era|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji|13=User:Immanuelle/Meiji era|qq=}} 3 (1870), calendrical duties were transferred to the Ministry of Education's {{ill|Astronomical Bureau|ja|天文暦道局|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Astronomical Bureau|qq=}}.

