== Observatories == The first observatory, '''Sitendai''', was established in [[:en:Jōkyō|Jōkyō]] 2 (1685) in {{ill|Ushigome Wakamachi|ja|牛込藁町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ushigome Wakamachi|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. It moved to [[:en:Surugadai|Kanda Surugadai]] in [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 14 (1701) and later to [[:en:Asakusa|Asakusa]]. In [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 13 (1842), a second observatory was established in {{ill|Kudanzaka|ja|九段坂|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kudanzaka|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 九段}}. Both were abolished in [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 2 (1869).
== Abolition of the Tenmonkata == After the {{ill|Taisei Hōkan|ja|大政奉還|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taisei Hōkan|qq=}}, responsibility for calendrical work returned to the {{ill|Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado clan|lt=Tsuchimikado family|ja|土御門家|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tsuchimikado family|qq=}}. In [[:en:Meiji era|Meiji era]] 3 (1870), calendrical duties were transferred to the Ministry of Education's {{ill|Astronomical Bureau|ja|天文暦道局|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Astronomical Bureau|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
