; Shibukawa Family : Owing to Shibukawa Shunkai's achievements, his family assumed the role of Tenmonkata in Jōkyō 1 (1684) and maintained the position, despite several adoptions, until the late Edo period. : [[:en:Shibukawa Shunkai|Shibukawa Shunkai]] – {{ill|Shibukawa Mukai|ja|渋川昔尹|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Mukai|qq=|1=Shibukawa Hisatada|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11561578}} – {{ill|Shibukawa Keiin|ja|渋川敬尹|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Keiin|qq=|1=Shibukawa Hirotada|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11561574}} – {{ill|Shibukawa Keiya|ja|渋川敬也|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Keiya|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 入間川重恒|1=Irumagawa Shigetsune|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11389078}} – {{ill|Shibukawa Noriyasu|ja|渋川則休|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Noriyasu|qq=|1=Shibukawa Noriyoshi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11561560}} – {{ill|Shibukawa Mitsuhiro|ja|渋川光洪|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Mitsuhiro|qq=|1=Shibukawa Mitsuhiro|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11561556}} – {{ill|Shibukawa Masakiyo|ja|渋川正清|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Masakiyo|qq=|1=Shibukawa Masakiyo|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11561581}} – {{ill|Shibukawa Masayō|ja|渋川正陽|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Masayō|qq=|1=Shibukawa Masateru|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11561582}} – {{ill|Shibukawa Keiyū|ja|渋川景佑|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Keiyū|qq=|1=Shibukawa Kagesuke|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11561577}} – ({{ill|Shibukawa Keichoku|ja|渋川敬直|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Keichoku|qq=|1=Shibukawa Hironao|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11561576}}) – {{ill|Shibukawa Sukemasa|ja|渋川佑賢|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shibukawa Sukemasa|q